{
  "texts": [
    "The conductivities are given by κ e = 3.1616 k B p e ν ei m e, (15) κ e ⊥ = k B p e ν ei m e 4.664x 2 e + 11.92 x 4 e + 14.79x 2 e + 3.77, (16) κ e × = k B p e ν ei m e x e 5 2 x 2 e + 21.67 x 4 e + 14.79x 2 e + 3.77, (17)",
    "where p e, p i, m e, and m i are the pressure and mass of each species and k B is the Boltzmann constant.",
    "The collisional frequency of ion-ion collisions is ν ii and of electron-ion collisions is ν ei.",
    "The quantities x e and x i represent the ratio between cyclotron frequency and collision frequency (ν) for electrons and ions, respectively",
    "and the collision frequencies are specified in Section 2.2, see also (Khomenko et al., 2014b)."
  ]
}